.TH CISV 1 "March 2026" "cisv-cli 0.4.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cisv \- high-performance CSV parser and writer CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cisv
[\fBCOMMAND\fR] [\fBOPTIONS\fR] [\fBFILE\fR]
.br
.B cisv
\fBwrite\fR [\fBOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcisv\fR is a high-performance CSV command-line tool backed by \fBcisv-core\fR.
It supports parsing, row counting, column selection, head/tail output, benchmarking,
and CSV generation through the \fBwrite\fR subcommand.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B parse
Parse a CSV file (default command when no command is provided).
.TP
.B write
Generate CSV output and benchmark writer throughput.
.SH PARSE OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show version.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-delimiter \fIDELIM\fR
Set field delimiter (default: \fB,\fR).
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quote \fICHAR\fR
Set quote character (default: \fB"\fR).
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-escape \fICHAR\fR
Set escape character.
.TP
.B \-m, \-\-comment \fICHAR\fR
Set comment character.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-trim
Trim whitespace from fields.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-relaxed
Enable relaxed parsing.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-empty
Skip empty lines.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-errors
Skip lines with parse errors.
.TP
.B \-\-strict
Stop on first parse error (default behavior).
.TP
.B \-\-no-header
Skip first row in output.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress non-data stderr logs.
.TP
.B \-\-max-row \fISIZE\fR
Set max row size in bytes.
.TP
.B \-\-from-line \fIN\fR
Start from line \fIN\fR (1-based).
.TP
.B \-\-to-line \fIN\fR
Stop at line \fIN\fR.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-select \fICOLS\fR
Select comma-separated column indices.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-count
Print row count only.
.TP
.B \-\-head \fIN\fR
Print first \fIN\fR rows.
.TP
.B \-\-tail \fIN\fR
Print last \fIN\fR rows.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Write output to file instead of stdout.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-benchmark
Run parser benchmark mode.
.SH WRITE OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-g, \-\-generate \fIN\fR
Generate \fIN\fR rows of synthetic CSV data.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Write output to file.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-delimiter \fICHAR\fR
Set output delimiter.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quote \fICHAR\fR
Set output quote character.
.TP
.B \-Q, \-\-always-quote
Always quote output fields.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-crlf
Use CRLF line endings.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-null \fISTRING\fR
Text to output for NULL fields.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-columns \fILIST\fR
Column names for generation mode.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-benchmark
Run writer benchmark mode.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Parse and print:
.B cisv data.csv
.TP
Count rows only:
.B cisv \-c data.csv
.TP
Select columns 0 and 2:
.B cisv \-s 0,2 data.csv
.TP
Parse stdin stream:
.B cat data.csv | cisv -
.TP
Generate one million rows:
.B cisv write \-g 1000000 \-o out.csv
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR awk (1),
.BR cut (1),
.BR sed (1)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/Sanix-Darker/cisv-cli
